{"word":"G3051 - λόγιον - lógion - log'-ee-on - Oracle","slug":"G3051","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">λόγιον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lógion"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>log'-ee-on"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Oracle"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>λόγιον</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Logion</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>log'-ee-on</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> a brief utterance, a divine oracle (doubtless because oracles were generally brief) </p> <p class='li520'><b>a.</b> in the NT, the words or utterances of God </p> <p class='li520'><b>b.</b> of the contents of the Mosaic law </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G3052\">G3052</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 06:17,5 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Noun Neuter <p />- Strong's: Neuter of <a href=\"#/G3052\">G3052</a>; an <i>utterance</i> (of God): - oracle. "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1586\">G1586</a>, <a href=\"#/G1588\">G1588</a>, <a href=\"#/G1589\">G1589</a>, <a href=\"#/G249\">G249</a>, <a href=\"#/G2980\">G2980</a>, <a href=\"#/G3004\">G3004</a>, <a href=\"#/G3050\">G3050</a>, <a href=\"#/G3052\">G3052</a>, <a href=\"#/G3054\">G3054</a>, <a href=\"#/G3055\">G3055</a>, <a href=\"#/G3056\">G3056</a>"}]}